## Download VS code (Optional)

[https://code.visualstudio.com/download](https://code.visualstudio.com/download)


## Download python 2.7

[https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-2718/](https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-2718/)


## Add python to Path



1. Navigate to your folder system
2. right click on the ‘**This PC**‘ icon. Then, select ‘**Properties**.’
3. click on the ‘**Advanced system settings**‘
4. click on the ‘**Environment Variables…**‘
5. click on `**Path**` then **‘edit’**
6. Click on **‘new’**
7. Add the location of python to your path ex “`c:\python27`”


## Installing the dependencies



1. Using the terminal navigate to where the script is located
2. Run the following command `python -m pip install pyserial`


## Running the script



1. Using the terminal navigate to where the script is located
2. Run the following command `python  main.py`


## Basic Commands


```
p1 = IRobot()
Create a new robotclass

p1.getSerialPorts()
Get the available ports

p1.connect('/dev/tty.usbserial-DN027Y2O')
Connect to the robot
p1.sendCommandASCII('128')
p1.sendCommandASCII('131')
p1.sendCommandASCII('140 3 1 64 16 141 3')
Check opt code documentation to understand above commands

p1.drive(200, 0) 
The drive function takes 2 parameter, first number is forward or backward
positive=foward
negative=backwward

Second parameter is tire rotation
positive=left
negative=right
